setAccessRuleOnInstance

void setAccessRuleOnInstance(AccessRule aRule)
Declares that global access to a data set may be restricted by the specified rule.

Attention: Only one rule can be associated with a data model regarding the access to its data sets. Thus, if a rule has previously been set using this method, it will be replaced by the current one.

Parameters:
aRule - specifies the rule to be set
See Also:
setAccessRuleOnNode(Path, AccessRule), setAccessRuleOnOccurrence(Path, AccessRule), AccessRule.getPermission(com.onwbp.adaptation.Adaptation, Session, SchemaNode)

setAccessRuleOnNode

void setAccessRuleOnNode(Path aPath,
                         AccessRule aRule)
Declares that the access to a node may be restricted by the specified rule.

Attention: Only one rule can be associated with a node. Thus, if a rule has previously been set on the node, it will be replaced by the current one.

At runtime, the effective access permission for a node is the most restrictive permission of the following:

  1. permission configured on the node: these are the rights on the node that are set or inherited;
  2. access rule for the node: these are the rights that are computed by the access rule attached to the node, as set by this method;
  3. access rule for the node's data set: these are the rights that are computed by the access rule attached to the data set containing the node (see setAccessRuleOnInstance(AccessRule));
  4. access rule for the node's record: these are the rights that are computed by the access rule attached to the record containing the node, if the node is in a table (see setAccessRuleOnOccurrence(Path, AccessRule)).
When a rule is not defined at a given level, it is considered to be AccessRule.ALWAYS_READ_WRITE at that level.

Note: An access rule cannot be defined on a sub-terminal node.

Parameters:
aPath - the location of the node on which to set the rule
aRule - specifies the rule to be set
See Also:
AccessRule.getPermission(com.onwbp.adaptation.Adaptation, Session, SchemaNode)

setAccessRuleOnNodeAndAllDescendants

void setAccessRuleOnNodeAndAllDescendants(Path aSubTreePath,
                                          boolean includeSubTreeRoot,
                                          AccessRule aRule)
Declares that the access to a node's subtree may be restricted by the specified rule.

Attention: Only one rule can be associated with a node. Thus, if a rule has previously been set for any node in the specified sub-tree, it will be replaced by the current one. For this reason, the order in which rules are set is important.

Parameters:
aSubTreePath - specifies the root of the sub-tree on which to set the rule
includeSubTreeRoot - specifies whether the root is also to have the rule set
aRule - specifies the rule to set
See Also:
setAccessRuleOnNode(Path, AccessRule), AccessRule.getPermission(com.onwbp.adaptation.Adaptation, Session, SchemaNode)

setAccessRuleOnOccurrence

void setAccessRuleOnOccurrence(Path aTablePath,
                               AccessRule aRule)
Declares that global access to a table record in the data model may be restricted by the rule specified.

Attention: Only one rule can be associated with a table at a given path for access to its records. Thus, if a rule has been already set, it will be replaced by the current one.

At runtime, the effective access permission to a table record is the most restrictive permission of the following:

  1. access rule for the table's data set: these are the rights that are computed by the access rule attached to the data set containing the table (see setAccessRuleOnInstance(AccessRule));
  2. access rule for the node's record: these are the rights that are computed by the access rule attached to the record containing the node, as set by this method.
When a rule is not defined at a given level, it is considered to be AccessRule.ALWAYS_READ_WRITE at that level.

Parameters:
aTablePath - location of the table node
aRule - specifies the rule to set
See Also:
AccessRule.getPermission(com.onwbp.adaptation.Adaptation, Session, SchemaNode)
